# LITIGATION CHRONOLOGY & LEGAL ISSUE ANALYSIS — COMPREHENSIVE
## 19 First Avenue (Freddie Sheene / Widegate Pty Ltd)
### Complete Analysis: 258 Project Emails + iMessage/WhatsApp Evidence

---

## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

This briefing package documents a pattern of conduct by Freddie Sheene (via Widegate Pty Ltd) regarding the 19 First Avenue high-rise development that gives rise to significant legal claims including breach of settlement deed, failure to meet financial obligations, statutory demand abuse, and potentially fraudulent conduct.

**Key Finding:** Freddie entered into a Deed of Settlement on July 23, 2025, requiring him to deposit $50,000 within 24 hours. By July 28, 2025, he had failed to make this payment despite his solicitors confirming the settlement. This constitutes a material breach of the settlement agreement.

**Immediate Risk:** The pattern of non-compliance with legal obligations, combined with previous statutory demand abuse and ongoing threats, demonstrates conduct that may justify urgent injunctive relief and damages claims.

